# Voice Assistant & Audio AI Projects - Development Rules

## Project Context
This folder contains 20 voice interaction, speech processing, and audio AI solutions.

## Technology Stack
- **Speech Recognition**: Google Speech-to-Text, OpenAI Whisper, Azure Speech
- **Text-to-Speech**: Google TTS, Amazon Polly, ElevenLabs
- **NLU/NLP**: Dialogflow, Rasa, OpenAI GPT, spaCy
- **Audio Processing**: Web Audio API, FFmpeg, librosa, pydub
- **Voice Platforms**: Twilio Voice, Vonage, WebRTC
- **Backend**: Node.js, Python (FastAPI, Flask)
- **Real-time**: WebSockets, Socket.io

## Development Guidelines

### Code Standards
- Implement proper error handling for audio processing
- Use async/await for all audio operations
- Handle microphone permissions gracefully
- Implement proper cleanup for audio resources
- Write modular, testable code

### Voice & Audio Best Practices
- Implement noise cancellation and audio enhancement
- Handle various audio formats and sample rates
- Optimize for low-latency processing
- Implement proper buffering strategies
- Handle network interruptions gracefully
- Support multiple languages and accents

### Speech Recognition Integration
- Implement streaming recognition for real-time feedback
- Handle partial and final transcription results
- Implement confidence scoring
- Support custom vocabulary and context
- Handle silence detection and endpoint detection
- Implement fallback mechanisms

### Text-to-Speech Integration
- Cache generated audio when appropriate
- Support SSML for advanced speech control
- Implement voice customization options
- Handle long text with proper chunking
- Optimize audio quality vs. file size

### Audio Processing Pipeline
```
Input → Preprocessing → Feature Extraction → AI Processing → Post-processing → Output
```

### Project Structure
```
project-name/
├── src/
│   ├── audio/          # Audio processing utilities
│   ├── speech/         # Speech recognition/synthesis
│   ├── nlp/            # Natural language processing
│   ├── services/       # External API integrations
│   ├── models/         # AI models
│   ├── utils/          # Helper functions
│   └── config/         # Configuration files
├── tests/              # Test files
├── audio-samples/      # Sample audio files for testing
└── package.json
```

### Testing Requirements
- Test with various audio qualities and formats
- Test with different accents and speaking styles
- Implement unit tests for audio processing functions
- Test real-time performance and latency
- Test error handling and edge cases
- Use mock audio data for automated testing

### Performance Optimization
- Implement audio streaming for large files
- Use Web Workers for heavy processing
- Optimize model inference time
- Implement caching for repeated queries
- Monitor memory usage with audio buffers
- Use appropriate audio compression

### Real-time Communication
- Implement WebRTC for peer-to-peer audio
- Use WebSockets for server communication
- Handle connection drops and reconnection
- Implement echo cancellation
- Optimize for low latency

### Security Considerations
- Encrypt audio data in transit
- Implement proper authentication for voice commands
- Validate voice biometrics securely
- Handle sensitive audio data with care
- Implement rate limiting for API calls

### Accessibility
- Provide visual feedback for audio interactions
- Support keyboard alternatives
- Implement clear error messages
- Provide transcripts for audio content
- Support assistive technologies

## Common AI Features
- Voice command recognition and intent detection
- Speech-to-text transcription
- Text-to-speech synthesis
- Voice cloning and customization
- Emotion and sentiment detection from voice
- Speaker identification and diarization
- Audio enhancement and noise reduction
- Real-time translation
- Meeting transcription and summarization

## Audio Format Support
- WAV, MP3, OGG, FLAC, AAC
- Sample rates: 8kHz, 16kHz, 44.1kHz, 48kHz
- Mono and stereo channels

